OL,3,CMan found guilty of murder and cruelty
OL,4,Cof partner's toddler son
OL,6,FCharlie's natural father saw his son
OL,7,Fonce a week and was described by the
OL,8,Fprosecution as "loving and caring".
OL,10,FSocial services were concerned about
OL,11,Fthe little boy's welfare at home with
OL,12,Fhis mother after he was taken to
OL,13,Fhospital in May 2023 with bruising,
OL,14,Fbut no action was taken at the time.
OL,16,FRoberts tried to explain that bruises
OL,17,Fon Charlie's ear months later were
OL,18,Fcaused by him resting on his toy box
OL,19,Fwhile he was sleep-walking or from
OL,20,Ffalling out of bed.
